Head (Fig. 
4
) dark brown, vertex sparsely covered by short, light hairs. Three ocelli almost in line, lateral ocellus placed 2.5 to 3 times its diameter from eye margin. Clypeus bud-shaped, 2x wider than long. Palpi 5-segmented, yellowish-brown. First three segments short, fifth segment 1.75-1.5 as long as fourth segment. Antenna with scape and pedicel usually largely brown, sometimes yellowish. Pedicel with outstanding apico-dorsal seta about as long as first flagellomere. Flagellomeres bearing light, curved, decumbent setulae, their length not exceeding width of respective flagellomeres.

The new species has a wide Palaearctic range in boreo-mountainous localities, it has been collected from the High North boreal forest of Fennoscandia (Norway, Finland, NW Russia), from a high mountain site in Asian part of Russia and from hummock tundra in Far East Russia, at a total of seven localities (Fig. 
2
).
